item.title: Help on Compiling rsclint423 (read plz)
item.dc:creator: @sdouble sdouble
item.description:
@sdouble wrote:

I’m seeing the rsclient*.java as the jar you get from the deobber? It’s actually, in this case, rsclient423.jar You don’t compile jar files, you compile java files. you would have to extract the jar file first using either winrar or the jar command ( jar xvf rsclient*.jar ) to get the .java files. Then you would compile them. ( javac *.java ) At this point, you could run it, although it won’t connect. you would have to make the change in the client.java file before you could compile it then connect. Browse through the client hacking sections, you’ll find it.

Enjoy.

Read full topic
